## Guardrail System Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
  A[User Query] --> B[Main Agent]
  B --> C[IsDataRelatedToHotels Object]
  C --> D[Guardrail Agent]
  D --> E[Validation Result]
  E --> F{Valid Hotel Content?}
  F -->|Yes| G[Return Response]
  F -->|No| H[Trigger Guardrail]
  style H fill:#f9d5d5,stroke:#ff5252
```

### Flow Explanation
1. **Main Agent** processes the query and generates an `IsDataRelatedToHotels` object
2. **Guardrail Agent** validates the object's contents
3. System checks validation result:
   - ✅ Valid: Returns the response
   - ❌ Invalid: Triggers guardrail (blocks response)

> **Note**: This ensures only hotel-related content passes through